@@TJvWaitingProgress.Active
Description:
if this property is true, the progress will increase until the maximum. Each time you set this property to true, the position is reseted.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWaitingProgress.Color

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWaitingProgress.Length
Description:
This is the maximum time you want to wait. This time is exprimed in milliseconds. After this delay, the event OnEnded>MAIN if fired and the active property is set to false.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWaitingProgress.OnEnded
Description:
This event is fired when the progression has finished. The active property is then set to false. Use this event to know if the user has waited the whole delay, and if you haven't stopped it.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWaitingProgress.ProgressColor
Description:
This is the color of the progress bar you want to see during the progression.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWaitingProgress.RefreshInterval
Description:
This is the refresh interval you want during the progression of the bar. Don't put this property to the minimum or it will probably blink and/or consume a lot of CPU !. Don't put this property to high, cause it could cause problems with the accuracy of the total duration.

